I'm not understanding the connection between this description and what this  service does.  It looks like it just forces the state to off?  Can you reword this description to be more informative?

The services in this repo are used for those gpios which must be initialized and monitored in phosphor-gpio-monitor.

These services depend on each project, so we named the repo as greatlakes gpio monitor register.

Prefer lower-kebab-case on service names.

Can you make the name on this more descriptive?
Please run something like `prettier` to format this file consistently.  I at a minimum see tabs and spaces and it seems to be using 8-space indentation when we typically use 4.
Why are we supplying a replacement for this service file?  Shouldn't this be added to the phosphor-gpio-monitor repository?

We should probably add an IMAGE_FEATURE to meta-phosphor to cover phosphor-gpio-monitor rather than adding it to the image as an EXTRA.

Can we add gratelakes-gpio-monitor-register as an RDEPENDS (via bbappend) on phosphor-gpio-monitor instead of explicitly adding it to the image?  That documents the reason.

We add phosphor-gpio-monitor into recipes-fb/packagegroups/packagegroup-fb-apps.bb

We will discuss how to implement the latter idea.
Did you intend to keep this in?  Why?

Currently, the led related services couldn't complete causing that multi-user.target never complete.

If multi-user.target doesn't complete, the obmc-host-startmin@.target couldn't start.

In that case, BMC couldn't set current host state to "Running".
What is this?  There is no such interface.

We push a commit to register this interface:
https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-gpio-monitor/+/58895
These should all be going into ${libexecdir}/${PN} and not into ${libexecdir} directly.  You can revisit that with a follow-up commit though.
Maybe "greatlakes gpio-monitor reactors"?  register is too ambiguous and doesn't describe what is going on here.  There isn't anything in this package that registers.

OK.

We will revise it with a more specific repo name.
Please add a comment then about this.  That is something we need to follow up with and get fixed.  It isn't obvious why we're removing it without a comment.

As mentioned elsewhere, this design isn't going to be acceptable.

See https://github.com/openbmc/docs/blob/f4febd002df578bad816239b70950f84ea4567e8/anti-patterns.md#dbus-interface-representing-gpios
